Source: vmdebootstrap
Section: admin
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Neil Williams <codehelp@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 8.0.0), python-support
Standards-Version: 3.9.4
Homepage: https://gitorious.org/vmdebootstrap
Vcs-Git: git://git.debian.org/collab-maint/vmdebootstrap.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/codehelp/vmdebootstrap-debian/debian

Package: vmdebootstrap
Architecture: any
Depends: debootstrap, extlinux (<< 3:6.00~), qemu-utils,
  parted, mbr, kpartx, python-cliapp, ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Bootstrap Debian into a (virtual machine) disk image
 vmdebootstrap is a wrapper around debootstrap to install Debian
 into a disk image, which can be used with a virtual machine (such as KVM).
